							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/davidwoo/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/David-Woo-headshot-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" alt="David Woo" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/davidwoo/">David Woo</a></h6>
										David Woo is the author of two collections of poetry, <em>Divine Fire</em> (University of Georgia Press) and <em>The Eclipses </em>(BOA Editions). His poetry and criticism have appeared in <em>The New Yorker</em>, the Poetry Foundation's <em>Harriet Books</em>, <em>The New Republic</em>, <em>Poetry London</em>, <em>The Threepenny Review</em>, and elsewhere. He lives in Phoenix and serves on the board of directors at the National Book Critics Circle.																			</div>
